result.execSummary:
The defendant David J Newby was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Endanger Safety/Use/Dangerous Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(a).
  • Operate Firearm While Intoxicated, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(b).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant David J Newby in court with attorney Travis Stephen Slattery.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Do not live with JC.  Absolute sobriety.  Do not possess any weapons.

Defendant David J Newby in court with attorney Travis Stephen Slattery.  Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Not guilty plea entered.  Bond continued.  Atty Slattery moves the court to lift the "no contact".  Jaleesa Cooks makes a statement regarding motion to lift "no contact".  Atty Slattery indicates that the parties would not be living with each other.  Atty Dominguez opposes the motion but would be agreeable to allow phone contact.  Court questions Newby regarding his medication.  Court lifts the "no contact" but does not want them to live together.

11:05 Defendant David J Newby in court with attorney Travis Stephen Slattery.  Derek Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Jason Dhein is sworn as a witness.  Testifies to his employment with Nekoosa Police Dept.  Testifies to responding to a call to Jaleesa Cooks residence on 12/21/14 regarding a domestic situation.  Testifies to conversation with Jaleesa Cooks.  Call came in from Newby's mother.  Cooks indicated that Newby stated something about killing himself and took several pills and had a firearm at one point.  Cooks also indicated that Newby stuck firearm to his temple and in his mouth.  Newby retreated to bathroom and fired the firearm.  Testifies to verifying that a handgun was fired in the bathroom.  Testifies to contact with Newby and how he identified himself.  Identifies David Newby in the courtroom.  Testifies to observations of Newby during conversation with him.  

11:17 Atty Slattery cross examines the witness.  Testifies to investigation into if there were people in the downstairs of building.  Testifies to where bullet went.  

11:21 Redirect by Atty Dominguez.  Testifies to recovering the firearm from Cooks who had taken it from Newby.  Gun was loaded.  

Atty Slattery present argument to not bind over for a felony.  Court finds probable cause and binds the matter over.
